    {"prompt": "Lenz's Law and Electromagnetic Braking — drop a magnet through a copper tube and it falls in slow motion. Eddy currents create opposing magnetic fields. No mechanical contact, yet the magnet practically floats down. Animate the induced currents and opposing force vectors.", "category": "physics_phenomena"},
