    {"prompt": "Rayleigh Scattering — why the sky is blue and sunsets are red. Short wavelengths scatter more (∝ 1/λ⁴). At noon, blue scatters toward you. At sunset, light travels through more atmosphere, scattering away all blue, leaving red. Animate photons scattering through the atmosphere.", "category": "physics_phenomena"},
    {"prompt": "Quantum Entanglement — measure one particle and you instantly know the other's state, no matter the distance. Einstein called it 'spooky action at a distance.' Bell's theorem proved it's real — no hidden variables. Animate the Bell test experiment and the violation of Bell's inequality.", "category": "physics_phenomena"},
    {"prompt": "The Piezoelectric Effect — squeeze certain crystals (quartz) and they produce voltage. Apply voltage and they deform. This is how quartz watches keep time: a tiny crystal vibrates 32,768 times per second. Animate the lattice deformation and the oscillator circuit.", "category": "physics_phenomena"},
