    {"prompt": "Neutron Stars and Nuclear Pasta — at the core of a neutron star, nuclear matter arranges into lasagna-like sheets, spaghetti-like tubes, and gnocchi-like bubbles. These are the strongest materials in the universe. Animate the density gradient from crust to core.", "category": "physics_phenomena"},
    {"prompt": "The Carnot Cycle — the maximum possible efficiency of any heat engine. Animate the four steps: isothermal expansion, adiabatic expansion, isothermal compression, adiabatic compression. Show why no real engine reaches Carnot efficiency and what entropy has to do with it.", "category": "physics_phenomena"},
